      "message": "This is the only place where secrets are actually used now. Unfortunately, getting rid of this or changing its format or changing the secrets themselves is extremely painful, since it would invalidate all outstanding tokens (stuff like CSRF tokens, CIPD upload session tokens, ResultDB \"signed\" URLs, PubSub auth tokens, etc). \n\nSo I\u0027m changing the interface in a way that would allow to keep using existing random/autogenerated secrets, as well as load previously stored secrets (Tink keys, OAuth client_secret).",
